	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, I have a guild PvP day coming up soon and have a large hatred for a particular fellow guildy. I will not go into my reasons as this hatred is admittedly a damper on my love for my daily EQ crack and would love to shove his fife up is a$$ and crush his bongos on his skull. <br><br>I would not have posted this had not a more directive post been made towards the class I am up against. Btw...excellent post Pusbag, hope you or any other fellow brethren of the class might be able to add a bit of wisdom to this .<br><br>By now I'm sure you will have realized who I am interested in turning into Shaman dust, if not, it is a Bard. I would not be so fearful of the class at lower lvl's but, being I am in my 40's and with a tint of embarrassment have little PvP experience,what might be some good strategies?<br><br>Here are the tactics I have in mind and my fears:<br><br>I plan on treating the Bard as a melee type even tho they do have a psudocasting ability by keeping them at a distance via throwing Blinding Luminance (Higher version of FoL for the young Shammies) on them canstantly as my most effective form of distance creator and allowing me to not need to mem Enstil (Root). My theory here being, most ppl when blinded never bother to run around like a headless chicken. This will allow me to thro Insidious Malady (Sicken) and Malisement for purposes of nonhealing abilities and allowing a greater chance of sticks for the upcoming DoT's. Med, rinse, lather, repeat as needed. <br>Now for the fear. I have an interest in using my pet on him in order to thro in some added damage, but, with his ability to charm, I no doubt do not want my pet to bite the hand that made it. I'm sure many of you in response might simply say, just don't use a pet, and, I of course am thinking this might be the best idea. But, my question now becomes, would it be possible to reverse this via my own Befriend Animal spell? Oh the trikiness of us Shaman <br>/e rubs hands together while giving the most wikid of grins.<br><br>Any info and thoughts regarding this thread would be ever so grateful, especially from anyone with experience in the field of shoving fife's up a$$' and crushing bongo's on skulls.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
