	   <tr><td colspan=2>Before Kunark no shaman would be cought dead with a 1hp weapon.&nbsp;&nbsp;After Kunark most shaman went with the Jade Chokidai Prod (damage 11 delay 30 wis +6) because it out damaged many of the old 2hb and gave more wisdom than any of the old 1hb.  Also since the epic weapon is a piercer many shaman feel the need to max piercering skill in the event they obtain one.  <br><br>To get the epic weapon you will need 3 groups of lvl 55+ not an easy thing to do, and in all my days I have only seen one shaman with one.  <br><br>Since SoV there are some 1hb that are better than the JCP, the dark ember for example.  Also there are some nice 1hb you can obtain at your lvl or shortly.  The Forest Giant Hammer from WW and the Sap of Piety (I forget the name of the zone, but it is off the WW zone).  <br><br>If you solo alot then a big 2hb is your best friend.  <br><br>What I am saying is that there is no longer any advantage of piercing weapon vs the 1hb or 2hb.  So ues the weapon type you like and get the best weapon you can of that type, or types.  <br><br>The best time to work on a low weapon skill is while in a group.  Also after lvl 24 and ever spell lvl after that the percent damage done by your weapon decresses, and therefore it is safer to improve lower weapon skills.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
