<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98280393619555></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98280393619555><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98280393619555>RE: 1 handed piercing weapons</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98280393619555#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Feb 21st 8:05 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>One- Yes the epic is a spear.&nbsp;&nbsp;Will you ever get it? The odds are against you.<br><br>Two- At higher lvls most groups are more lacking in melee than mana.  As a shaman I often tank while hunting in small groups.  I have been in a number of high lvl groups with only one melee class memeber.  If you are doing more melee damage than your tank, your tank has some serious problems.  If you are taking too much damage root the mob and back off.<br><br>Three-Our primary job is to make the group stronger.  Sometimes the group need mana and sometimes the group needs melee.  A well developed shaman can provide either.  My point is that a well equiped and developed Shaman can melee well enough to make a diffrence.  Rule of thum: if there are less than three tanks, odds are you should be meleeing as well as buffing  and debuffing.  <br><br>Bottom line- mana is a function of equipment and not of skill, while melee is a function of skill You will need to make a real effort to keep your melee skills maxed.  If you do it right you can cast the normal shaman spells and melee in most groups.  <br><br>Live large my Friend<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
