	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, all this is pretty good advice. The newbie zone stopped giving me exp at about lvl 5 too, What I did was to sloly move out of the newbie zone toward the tundra until I reached the edge of it, being careful not to bite off more than I could chew. It worked pretty well, and there are gaurds just inside the exits to the tundra in the valleys. Well, when I hit level 7, I moved to Blackburrow, and got in usually a two person group. Then we just <u>carefully</u> took out the gaurds right by the zone. Always listen for trains, as they are quite often lethal in this zone. When I was close to getting level 9, I got ported over to Gfay on Faydwer and hunted in Crushbone. I suggest buying your level 9 spells before doing this though, as they are tough to get on Faydwer. Crushbone is a very profitable zone to hunt in, just be careful for the trains. One of the best aspects of Crushbone is the quests, so don't neglect them. One of the best at these levels is the Orc Slaver quest to free the slaves. ALso eventually, I was able to get myself a Screaming Mace, which is a very nice weapon. So thought it is tough to get shaman spells on Faydwer, the hunting is some of the best for lower levels. That is just what I did, and it worked out really well for me.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Dirkin Youreye<br>Barbarian Shaman <br>23nd Level SoW's Available!!<br>"Fallen Eagles" Quellious Server</td></tr>
