<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98312814420450></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98312814420450><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98312814420450>RE: Melee or Mediate</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98312814420450#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2076><span id=Sage>Pusbag</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>1249 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Feb 25th 2:09 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.72]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You haven't clued us in as to what level you are and that is critical in the different stages of a shammy's life in terms of which choice you will make in any given situation.<br>Early in life you HAVE to melee since your mana pool is so limited, but that changes as you get older, so depending on the type of group you may do either.&nbsp;&nbsp;For instance, if there is a chanter with you who can dispense crack to the magic-eaters, you might be able to do both.  But if you are the primary healer or slower-downer you probably will be medding to facilitate the tanks doing their job more efficiently.  If there is a cleric on board you may be able to slow down the mob and then jump in and knock some heads together, while leaving the healing to the Doc.<br><br>Then there is the issue of spells and how they change your style as you acquire them.  Different spells in different times of your life make you adjust your mana usage so there is not the downtime from medding due to you having to cast just to save your skin.<br><br>It all depends, see?  And it all hinges on where you are in your levels.<br><br>I will say this, however, keep your hand in some melee combat all through your life since that will keep your defensive skills up and that adds to your armor class.  Armor class, as we all know, keeps the hits inflicted on you from damaging you as much as they could.  These little details can be the difference between life or death in a close battle-- and we all know how often those happen!<br><br>If we can get Gorthin to ever post again he could give you a detailed account of how he did it.  He is one of the most articulate posters on The Life of a Shaman that I have read in any board.  He's good.<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
