	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Feb 24th 2:53 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Being high lvl in EQ does not mean you know all there is to know about the class you play; it only means you have spent alot of time playing that class. <br>I am the one who posted after Shjekai, and my shaman is not low lvl.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you want to know my lvl you can calculate it from the following infomation.  If I hold a Mortiticators Staff instead of the JCP and CGS I will have 28 fewer mana points.  <br><br>I never said that a shaman can tank as well as a melee class.  What I am saying that if a Shaman keeps his melee skill up he can help the group with more than just his mana. <br><br>The following examples are from recent groups I have been in.  <br><br>Group one. 1 warrior, 2. shaman, 1 cleric, 1 druid and one wiz.  I was the seconed shaman to join the group.  Since this was a grop lacking in melee I started meleeing.  For the last fight not counting my pet I did 21% of the melee damage.  The normal shaman spell were split between myself and the other shaman. Because I was canablizing (druid was casting group regen) I was able to have the same amout of mana as the other shaman, who meditated druing combat.  Therefore my melee did not slow the group any.  <br><br>What did my meleeing do for the group?  Since the mob took 21% more damage druing the same amount of time the mob died 21% faster, the tank took 21% less damage, and the cleric had to heal 21% less.  And yes I was also casting my P dot. So the group killed more mobs in less time.  Isn't that the idea<br><br>Group two.  <br>2 War, 1 Paly, 1 cleric, 1 mage, and myself.  <br>This is a much more blanced group. For the most part I played the normal shaman. Buffing and debuffing and back up heal.  I kept regen on myself and canablized.  I was able to keep my mana equil to the others and still melee.  Mostly because the tanks far outclassed the mobs.  I also did crowd controll and would root on a dubble pull, I would then slow the Mob attacking the tank and slow and dot the rooted mob and then reroot.  That way when the mob came free it would attack me instead of the cleric.  If the other mob was near dead, I would melee the mob until the tanks finished up the first one. If not I would reroot.  <br><br>As far as shaman taking lots of damage druing group combat it just dosent happen that often.  In a group I cast slow as soon as the mob is in range.  So I take the first few hits.  I will also cast a P dot early if I'm in a melee limited group.  And I may take a few more hits.  However it isn't long before the mob is back on the tank.  If I'm taking too much damage I just root and back off<br><br><br>If a shaman makes the effort and keeps his melee skill up he can help a group by meleeing.  <br><br>I am glad you use the dots Verent gave us, I do as well.  Under the right conditions I also use the great melee weapons Verent has give the shaman class. <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
