	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just the replies here are proof positive of the many ways we can play our shamen.<br><br>I hunt with a primary partner (paladin), and when we create groups, they usually consist of two to three tanks (depending on what we're hunting), cleric, shaman, enchanter.&nbsp;&nbsp;Cleric heals and has some very sweet buffs (nice to have around in those out of the way places, too, in the event of an untimely death of a group mate).  Shaman buff tanks, sow all,  root, slow and dot mobs, send in the dog,  and backs up heals for cleric when necessary.  Enchanter keeps clarity on casters, quick on tanks and is there to mez in the event of a bad pull.  (if we can't get a cleric, we'll get a druid who can share heal duty with shaman.  If we can't get an enchanter, we'll get a bard)<br><br>When I was lower lvl, I tanked like a maniac. Now my group DOESN"T WANT me in the melee.  The little damage I inflict with my jade prod is pathetic and basically useless against the mobs we're hunting at this lvl.  My dog does more dmg than I do in melee.  But I do try and get in there and melee when I can.<br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>54 Barbarian Shaman (Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>35 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
