	   <tr><td colspan=2>At all levels a Shamans power is in his/her mana. As you get to higher levels your tanking ability will rapidly deminish as you see tanks getting more attacks and more powerful attacks. The only time I melee at all at level 51 and grouped is when I am standing up to Cannibalize. Other than that I am always sitting. I am needed to Slow and maybe heal. Buffing group memebers from time to time as well. It is a waste of everyones time when the pulls have to slow down because I am LOM. I also play a monk and nothing frustrates me more than watching the druid or enchanter or who ever in melee and then hear at the end of the fight or even during it, LOM or OOM. Know you role in a group. If you want to do things that you are not designed to do then please solo. You hinder the abilities of a group when you never have the mana to help the group as a whole. What good is a cleric that cannot heal, or a chanter that cannot mez or buff? As casting classes level they become much more specialized in their group tasks. Get used to&nbsp;&nbsp;it and learn how to help the group. Learn how to act as a whole. Don't be selfish. Shaman cannot melee at higher levels regardless of your weapon. Just look at the damage output of the tanks in your group compared to yours. However standing and throwing an Ebolt from time to time IS impressive. At 51 I am glad to sit while the tanks go to work. I slow and I heal a little. Buff a bit and maybe DoT. That is my job. <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
