<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98295806978247></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98295806978247><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98295806978247>RE: what should i be</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98295806978247#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=33540><span id= >sdnelson</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>3 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Feb 23rd 2:54 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm not in a PvP server, but I have taken up tailoring, for some simple reasons.<br><br>1) it's an easy way to get armor.&nbsp;&nbsp;Make it.<br>2) The large tailoring kit and many patterns are for sale just inside the gate to Halas.  Other patterns are for sale at Mac's Kilts.<br>3) There is great availability of pelts in Everfrost.  You don't have to go far to fill your pack with ruined bear pelts.<br>4) Being a tailor will help you do the Gnoll Fur Bundle quest in Halas and get the Fang of the North a magical piercing weapon, not a great weapon, but not bad either.<br>5) Turn all the spiderling silks you get into silk threads, then combine two silk threads to get a silk bandage.  Either sell these to monks or use them to pump up your bind wounds skill.<br>6) Turn all the spider silks you get into silk swatches, then when you're tailoring skill is higher you can turn these into silk armor.  Sell it to monks in Qeynos or Freeport for some good money.<br><br>Between tailoring and turning in polar bear pelts to Cindl in Mac's Kilts I had a full set of tattered armor by level 4, plus I had sold a number of pieces for profit.  In addition to just selling the armor for profit you can outfit newbies in exchange for pelts to keep your skill level up.  They'll appreciate the armor and be glad to free up a slot from carrying an 8cp item (ruined pelt).  The first group I was in was people that I had given armor to, it's a great way to make friends.<br><br>Blacksmithing is another good skill as you will eventually be able to make the barbarian only cultural Ringmail armor, and use your Imbue skill to imbue ivory and create imbued armor and weapons that only barbarians can wield.<br><br>Good luck with it.<br>&nbsp;<br>Wulfgyr, Barbarian Shaman of Torvonillous</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
