	   <tr><td colspan=2>Now, this is not a diatribe against twinking-- I have done it, you have done it, and if you pay your 10 bucks I believe you should be able to do what you want with your character.&nbsp;&nbsp;But for those who rail against the evils of "hand-me-downs" I offer this solution:<br><br>If Verant had made most items that are found on mobs unsellable except to merchants and made items which are manufactured by the individual tradeable then the artificial market would remain stable and inflation, deflation, and twinking would not occur.  The game would remain "pure" in the sense of what it once was when it began.  The cheaper armors and weapons would regain their value and skills like Blacksmithing would get prices which reflected the time and effort put into them.<br>What do you think?<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
