	   <tr><td colspan=2>Oh, this is too funny&nbsp;&nbsp;:)   Been there, done that.  It took me forever to learn my way around Everfrost.  My suggestion is that you print yourself a map of the zone if you haven't done so already.  And always be aware of where you are.  If you get into trouble, die fighting and not fleeing for your life.  Finding your corpse is much easier this way (I remember running blindly from a vengeful composer at lvl 4, in a panic, to the top of a peak and down the other side.  Fortunately, there was a necro in the zone who was more than happy to help me find myself).  [you have become better at dying (999)]   lmao   This is the time to die, friend, when you have no worries about exp loss  :)  Sure, corpse runs are a menace, but no biggie right now [you have become better at looting (999)]<br> <br>You might consider hunting somewhat close to the ramp until you make lvl 5.  If memory serves, lvl 5 or 6 was when all the polar bear cubs finally stopped aggroing me (incidentally, the vengies still aggro to me at lvl 40, the fools.  lol).  By the time you hit lvl 4, however, you'll be able to take on a whole pack of the bears, whelps and gnoll pups with no problem.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>54 Barbarian Shaman (Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>35 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
