<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9816669888741></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9816669888741><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9816669888741>RE: KOS</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=9816669888741#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=20729><span id= >CompBoy</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>11 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Feb 8th 9:20 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am an ogre shammy of 17, almost 18 levels, now (sad to say, that is my main character.) Anyways, the best thing you can probably do is head to the Innothule Swamp, and kill with the trolls. However, before you do, make SURE to get SoW, or else you will probably be ogre goo much sooner than you might think. One of the things you need to remember is to avoid the Human than is slightly west of the Grobb zone. Another thing is to head right from the Feerrott, once you zone, and hug the wall. You can go into the water if you want, but just to be safe, you should just stay high and dry. Once you get to the higher levels (upper single digits) you can make your way towards Guk. Now, you have to be careful, cause there is a big step from killing n00b frogloks (keep those fleshies, and give them to the guild master in Oggok. He gives you Burst of Flame, a lvl 1 spell, for every 4 of those you get.) It can be helpful if you can get some buffs, at the very least a SoW, or group up (unless you got an uber friend to help, or you are twinked. I have seen lvl 3s solo the froglok guards.) After the froglok guards are blue/green to you, it can ge a good idea to head to Southern Ro (take the wall right of the entrance to Guk, if you are heading out of it.) Be careful of the building you pass, cause there are zombies that spawn, as well as a BUNCH of aligators (that are stuck in the building.) So, once you are in SRo, you should kill orcs for a while. If you are soloing, you should try the camp of 2 that is near the Druid ring (I think it is slightly west of the ring.) Once they become easier to solo, and are bad exp, it is time to move on to dervs. However, at this point, you can probably go to NRo, because there are LOTS of derv groups (at least on Povar.) I have a friend who was a lvl 8 High Elf Cleric that was in a group. I think you do that until about 12 or 13. Then, you head onto Oasis. From here, it is probably a good idea to get a croc group. The bad part is usually there are hardly any around, although they give the most exp. I suggest having a ranger in your group to track them down. I am lvl 17, and am still killing Crocs and DW caimen. The regular Caimen are green, and DW Crocs are red. An alternative to that is to hunt at the orc highway. You do have to be careful of the "a orc warriors" because they are lvl 20+. Another warning is to look out for Sand Giants, and Spectres that get loose. Probably one last thing to remember is to avoid taking MOBs that are overwhelming you to the docks. Lots of them are around lvl 15-20, although some are upper 30s, and even 40s. Point is, they can't take all of what you dish out. Especially Specs and SGs (seen a LOT of corpses from that kind of stuff.) Well, after you get to about lvl 20, maybe a little earlier, you can head over to Kunark. You can TRY killing in the Overthere, although it is probably better to kill in the Lake of Ill Omen. Just be careful in OT, cause at night, stuff comes out that is pretty high lvl, not to mention the Kunark Rhinos (faster than SoW.) I think another place to kill is Lake Rathe.<br>Well, hope that helps you for a while. If you ever play on Povar, try lookin me up. <br><br>Oumlagar of the Dark Legion<br>Shammy of the 17th buff<br><br>P.S. Sorry it was such a long post. It just happens when I have a lot to say =)<br>&nbsp;<br>Welcome to the Dark Legion!<br>May the pain and suffering of others bring you pleasure.</td></tr>
